text: It’s so important to clarify that the energy and effort we both put in is equal and that’s why our duties and expectations shift in harmonious ways!
Yes, my kids did their own laundry by age 10. Now that the kids are grown he still does his own laundry and I do mine.
My husband does dishes, I do laundry. We took the top two most awful jobs and nice split them 🤣
We have a maid for that because I work 60+ hour weeks and am not spending my time on housekeeping.
A big part of the issue in my marriage was me being overwhelmed bc my ex didn’t help much with household chores. And we both worked outside the house the same amount.
I feel that is a GREAT injustice and one that is way too common
SAHM stay-at-home-mom not stay at home maid or stay at home chef
I too, taught all 4 of my kids by age 8 to do their own laundry. It's a life skill. I had to let go of everything put away or hung up but didn't care as long as it was neatly in their room.
I had to learn right before college and that was dumb. My kids are fully capable and will continue to learn more duties and skills to participate in the family and gain independence
I transfer my hubbys laundry, and he’ll transfer mine . And then we fold them together. In fact he was kind enough do fold and put away all mine the other day because I work 2 jobs and I was tired.
My husband do all our laundry 🤭
my husband does laundry on weekends if needed but usually I do his laundry because we mix it. 🤣 one basket, when it's full it gets washed.
Every person in my home dies their own laundry…..why wouldn’t they if they are old enough. It’s a basic human responsibility.
Agreed
My job as a sahm/homeschooler is keeping kids alive/fed/educated/etc. Everything else is split duties.

I'm a SAHM & I hardly ever do my hubs laundry. His words "I've been doing my own laundry since I was 10. I'm not gonna stop just because we're married now." Obviously if he needs me too I will though.
If I’m doing chores, I’ll include my husband but it’s not my JOB to do his stuff.
We both did laundry at first, but he works way more hours outside of the house. I don’t deal with the lawn, leaves, pool or car stuff. We our partners.
SAHM here too! I don't do my husbands laundry either! Similar to you, I used to, then I had more/more and that was something he could take over!
Exactly!
I wash and dry, he folds and puts it away

Love this! My husband & I both work, he does the cooking, I do the laundry and we help each other where we can. It doesn’t matter if it is a male or female role job, we are a partnership & get it done
💯 Teamwork!
I run almost all our laundry. My husband folds almost all if it. The folding is MUCH more work
I do hate folding
Yesssss. To the kids doing laundry!! And doing the things and equal labor!!!! Love it!!
I’m with you. The rule is we do our own. Every now and then we do each other’s.
The split of duties should be in any marriage regardless of stay at home mom or Work outside of the home mom
I'm now working since our youngest is in school (I'm a substitute teacher at their district, often for their school). We always split things. We do our laundry together,we both cook, do dishes etc.
Unrelated, but your skin is glowing!! 🥰🥰
I wash and dry the laundry, but it’s his job to put it up.

A stay at home mum role is to raise the children, the dads role is to work and then household chores are 50/50 with either picking up the slack when the other is sick or away! SAHM is a full time job if you’re doing it right!
I feel the same way!
I wish I'd known about equal rest, not equal labor. I had 18 hour days, he came home from the office and maybe read a bed time story.
I do the laundry and I often “have to fold laundry” when it’s time to give the little one a bath so he does that instead 🤷🏼‍♀️works for me
We have a community basket in our house. Everyone’s dirty laundry goes into one. We both do laundry so whoever’s is in the basket get washed. It has worked wonders for us!
My husband does all of the laundry and the dishes! 💅🏻 I only stay home during the summer though. He does that year round.
Yes 👏🙌
How is laundry bad? It literally takes less than 5 minutes to load the washer and swap to dryer when it’s done.
And folding and putting away for a family of 5. Bedding once a week and daily towels.
We skipped the folding part we have a bed/chair for the clean laundry 😅
We have this agreement too: he is 100% dishes for everyone and I’m 100% laundry for everyone. It works for us
I had this agreement with my ex, but somehow, I ended up doing dishes too...
As someone who had to teach a 19yr old bf how to do laundry because his mom did EVERYTHING for him… THANK YOU
Same! I could have juggled it if he’d picked up after himself & taken out the trash. Eventually I quit doing his laundry and making meals for anyone other than myself & my kids. 4yr free now
Partnership people
Mine, too!
Mine too, it’s great!
my husband typically washes and dries the clothes then I fold them 😂 we both do dishes now that we have a dish washer and I cook. it works for us, our 3 year old helps clean up age appropriately😂
I’m still working on my 2.5 year old 😂
Kids doing their laundry is the best. If they take it upstairs, don’t fold it, and let it get wrinkled, it’s on them. Lol.
My husband and kids do their own laundry too, also a SAHM
My mom had us doing our own laundry and making our own school lunches by 8.
I’m in agreement with you. But also my husband does my laundry. 🥰
Totally respect the dynamic, but I hate the thought of running a half filled washer just for 1 persons clothes. We’ll throw our clothes in the same pile and we all help folding/running loads.
My husband & I both work & share the domestic responsibilities. Except mowing the lawn & cleaning our bathroom, he prefers to mow & I prefer to clean the bathroom.
Fam of 3, we all have our own hampers & do our own laundry. My hubby cooks, I clean, son does the trash.
Sounds like a great team 👍🏻
Yes. I’m a SAHM of 1 and I don’t do ANY laundry. My husband washes, folds, and puts away for all of us because it was something he could take off my plate.
I run my husband’s laundry, but I do not fold/put away any of it. But not because it’s “my job” but because I own watching the laundry bins and washing what is in the most need.
Yes! I don’t so my husband’s or my kids’ laundry. The kids did their own at 6 yrs. We are very equal partners. We naturally ebb and flow.
I do laundry because I like doing it and I'm good at it. my husband does dishes because I hate it. we revisit often where the division of labor should be and what our needs are as the kids change.
I’m with you! I would rather do laundry than dishes
I have not seen your videos in a while
I’ve been here 😁
Yeah my husband does his own laundry lol
Agree with you, Lisa! Whatever works for each couple equally. Making assumptions about “duties” is a no-no. I’m currently on a long mat leave (14 months) and doing more at home…but my husband still
I didn’t even recognize you with the light hair!
I think I’m going back dark! I wanted one more hurrah as a blonde
Hahahaha me either. My crippling adhd I forget 😂
My husband‘s a firefighter and home about 50% of the month. When he’s gone, I do all the laundry when he’s home. He does all of our laundry kids and mine.
My husband does his own laundry. It’s one of few things he does do. Though he tends to leave it in the dryer
my husband also doesn't do my laundry unless I asked him to.
Same, Lisa! Sometimes I throw his laundry in when I get the chance but he mostly does his own. Doing laundry for 3 little kids is a lotttt 😅 I hardly get that accomplished 😂
Yep! Me too! Constantly behind on laundry
I only do it occasionally if he is super busy or if it is a mixed load.
Yep! Me too
People just need to figure out what works for them and quit listening to people online 🤣🤣🤣 every marriage and relationship and family is different
Can you do a video of what is under your wheelhouse as a SAHM? I’m curious
My bf and I both work, we each do our own laundry unless asked to help. His 16 year old also does his own laundry. Laundry is a much more manageable task when it’s not 1 person trying to do 2+ loads
Equity not equality… both parents active in household work. Everyone is crating the need for the work so everyone should participate.
I’m not married, but my Bf and I live together at the moment and he does the laundry and I do all the cooking and kitchen clean up. He handles all the other cleaning duties. This set up works for us
My man is my stay at home husband. I honestly don’t even know where my clothes are. I LOVE him for what he does!!!
I’m realizing my husband and I never even discussed it when we first moved in together but he does his own and I do mine 😂.
I do my own, teen was taught to do his and hubs is particular about his so he does his own as well. it makes life happier in this house
YES! That sounds like how my husband and I do it too. We have two little kids and we're still overwhelmed.😂 I have no idea how people are surviving if only one person is doing the majority.
Well there ya go. Our households are run differently. Laundry takes more time and effort in my house
And it simplifies the organizational process.
Does a lot, too. And knows things will change when I go back to work full time. In some ways, the fact the pandemic hit when our 1st was a baby was a blessing in terms of the division of labor

Conversations—he would take our son to childcare each day, I would do pick up. He would put away laundry or dishes or put them on…and so would I. I usually cook, but he always does garbage. None of it
With a prompt, by the way. 🙌🏻
My brother used to do that when we shared a house… eventually he got tired of his clothes being on his bed or on top of the Xbox after the 100th time asking to set timers 🤣
My husband is a first responder as well - he does all the laundry in the house, including mine. It was just an easy chore for him to have that he’s able to do with his schedule.
Ran out of characters. 2+ people’s worth of loads
Do it don't do it all I'm gonna tell you is as a woman who has been married happily to the same man for 30 years keeping score doesn't benefit anyone
My husband does laundry on the weekend for the whole house 🤣I stay at home and homeschool kids, I also man the brunt of the cooking he cleans up dishes at night, I do dishes during the day
It’s just the 2 of us and prefer laundry over dishes. So he dose dishes and I do laundry
we both work. no kids. he does all the laundry 🙌

I’m not a stay at home. Mom never really was but I have still never done my husband’s laundry unless I need to get it out-of-the-way and he doesn’t want me doing his laundry because he says I’m not his mother.
I do my husband's laundry because I don't like the way he uses the laundry room and tossing his clothes in w/mine & kiddo's is easier than sharing the space 😂
Everyone is different but this just seems so weird. My wife and I share the household chores. The laundry is just laundry. We don’t separate clothes by who owns them
My husband takes the dirty clothes hamper to the laundry room.
I do my husband's laundry because of his work hours, but he has never once complained when I didn't do it because he understands it's a favor and not my job 🙃
My kids have their own chores my older two do trash and clean the bathrooms my youngest brings all of our laundry to the laundry room we are a community and we help each other.
I don’t do my husbands laundry most of the time either.
I handle the laundry in the house mostly because I'm a weirdo that enjoys laundry. 🤷‍♀️
My husband puts it in and I fold and put away. He works from home so he’s able to help when he’s on breaks
I think I was doing my own laundry around 8. I enjoyed the control out have me over my own things. It's awesome you are teaching them independence!
i never did his laundry but will occasionally fold
My ex never helped round the house in 23 yrs of marriage lol
so all our laundry gets washed together with the childrens clothes. but my husband washes the dishes and I pay for the cleaning ladies
How is this even a question? It didn’t even cross my mind to do someone else’s laundry. I wash my own dishes too. Like where’s this coming from?
I don’t usually do my husbands laundry either and really never have
I only do it if I have a small load. He folds all of it
I do my husband’s laundry but I like doing laundry and he’s very grateful 🤷‍♀️. 2 of the kids do their own, the youngest helps out.
Imo I’m going to work for 12-14hours. While I’m gone she does everything she can get done. If there’s still things to do when I get home we finish it.

I'm not understanding and neither is my wife.. she is saying if she's doing laundry what is the difference if she does all the laundry🤣🤣 that's like saying if I'm making dinner I'll only make it for me!🤣 or if she is making the bed she only makes half the bed! I'm a grown man and I don't expect my wife to do plenty of things but she will say u all are going nuts!! oh and she works🤣🤣
I do the laundry but he does the activities runs, he also picks up a lot of the extra stuff, cooking for guests, birthday cakes etc
Some people’s parents do everything for them or they expect the at home partner to do all the “at home” work. I’ve had to teach partners how to do laundry and sweep floors because they legit hadn’t 📍
📍been taught any of the necessary life skills
Well, this is likely because you have never been required to uphold misogynistic standards of what it means to be a woman or a girl. Who are expected and trained to be domestic servants from day one
We’re too lazy to divide our laundry. I see my sister do ALL her family’s laundry (5 people). She’s a freaking school principal and her lazy ass husband does NADA. 💔
I AM all for equal rights however I disagree with this. I think the person staying at home should handle domestic duties for both people like laundry because in this economy if the other partner is
My husband does all of it. He does a phenomenal job, and just because the gender norm would be for the me to do it, doesn't mean that's how it needs to be.>>
I’m a stay at home mom but my partner does 85% of the laundry. Because he can bust it out whereas I have toddlers following me around causing mayhem.
Not to mention you’re their teacher. 🤓
Yes! But that’s new for us…and things are again, shifting
I would still do yours... this is so petty
I do laundry, dishes, pool, dogs, vacuum and toilets. He cooks and takes care of the 2.5 acres including our garden. He also coaches the kids teams and handles their sports.
I left a pen in my husband once now his clothes wash themselves.
Maybe he should only do his own earning.
no one would blink if a man said he didn't do his wife's laundry.
I stopped doing my husbands laundry and making his lunches. Usually. Sometimes I do them. We are working on teaching my 8 yr old to do some stuff. I didn’t know this was a big deal.
I’m a sahm and I very rarely do my husbands laundry. I also rarely do my teenage son’s laundry. Soon my 10 year old will do his own.
Stay at home mom-do kids laundry. Not stay at home wife.
It’s not about whether or not those kind of men CAN do household chores. It’s that they don’t want to and see it as “woman’s work” while they just bring home a paycheck and nothing else.
😳 I do my family’s laundry, but my mom works 50ish hr a week and I work about half- it’s part of my “rent”
I’m sure she appreciates it very much! It’s SO much work. My sister also plans, shops for, and cooks all the meals. And cleans up. Basically all the household labor. It’s infuriating.
It’s not sustainable either. At some point she will burn out. Help where and when you can and encourage her.
The only one working, they’re likely working crazy long hours and taking on the crazy stress and responsibility of supporting both financially so why wouldn’t one give back by doing their laundry?
This goes both ways in my mind. When I’m the breadwinner my partner does all of our cooking and laundry and takes care of our dog 💙🐶 to make up for the difference
I struggled for 7 years to keep up with it, we finally gave in and just switched it up. He does it all, I just show up to help put it away. It's something that he is really good at>>
I have other talents to use to keep out household functioning. Doing what works best for our family is the way we roll.
They’re such… helpers 🤣🤣🤣 but soon they really will be helpful. We started around 4/5 helping put laundry in and pulling it out of the dryer all supervised, then folding 💙
